WEBVTT

00:02.520 --> 00:03.920
<font color="#ffff00">Queen Victoria.</font>

00:03.960 --> 00:07.760
<font color="#00ffff">If anything should happen to her,</font>
<font color="#00ffff">you are the heir to the throne.</font>

00:07.800 --> 00:10.000
Now that I'm Queen, I do not need
your assistance.

00:10.040 --> 00:11.640
<font color="#00ff00">This is not a game!</font>

00:11.760 --> 00:13.920
You offered to act as my private
secretary.

00:13.960 --> 00:15.360
<font color="#ffff00">I would be honoured ma'am.</font>

00:15.400 --> 00:17.720
<font color="#00ffff">The Queen has put me in charge of</font>
<font color="#00ffff">the household.</font>

00:17.760 --> 00:20.000
<font color="#00ff00">So we're answerable to a governess?</font>

00:20.040 --> 00:21.760
I want to dance with you.

00:21.920 --> 00:24.400
<font color="#00ff00">Your daughter has always been</font>
<font color="#00ff00">unstable.</font>

00:24.600 --> 00:26.680
You have always looked at him first,
then me!

00:26.920 --> 00:29.320
<font color="#ffff00">Through you I've been given a reason</font>
<font color="#ffff00">to continue.</font>

00:29.520 --> 00:32.200
I shall smile in the future with your
help Lord M.

00:32.759 --> 00:38.160
# Gloriana

00:39.160 --> 00:44.320
# Hallelujah

00:45.360 --> 00:51.120
# Gloriana

00:51.760 --> 00:56.920
# Hallelujah

00:57.920 --> 01:04.239
# Gloriana, hallelujah

01:04.280 --> 01:11.000
# Hallelujah!

01:11.480 --> 01:13.280
<font color="#ffff00">MAN IN CROWD:</font>
<font color="#ffff00">Long live the Duchess!</font>

01:13.320 --> 01:15.200
(Cheering)

01:15.240 --> 01:17.640
<font color="#00ffff">WOMAN IN CROWD:</font>
<font color="#00ffff">Long live the Duchess of Kent!</font>

01:19.640 --> 01:22.160
<font color="#00ff00">WOMAN IN CROWD:</font>
<font color="#00ff00">God save the Duchess!</font>

01:23.520 --> 01:27.800
I am concerned about my niece's
state of mind,
Wellington.

01:27.840 --> 01:32.560
She seems incapable of taking care
of the business of government.

01:32.600 --> 01:35.240
<font color="#ffff00">WELLINGTON:</font>
<font color="#ffff00">I believe they call her Mrs</font>
<font color="#ffff00">Melbourne.</font>

01:35.280 --> 01:38.760
<font color="#ffff00">He may be the Queen's favourite but</font>
<font color="#ffff00">that's no reason why the country</font>
<font color="#ffff00">should suffer.</font>

01:38.800 --> 01:43.480
<font color="#ffff00">It's hard to know if he is her</font>
<font color="#ffff00">minister or her nursemaid.</font>

01:43.520 --> 01:49.280
Indeed. He is altogether too
indulgent of my niece's unstable
temperament.

01:49.320 --> 01:52.720
<font color="#00ffff">Are you suggesting that the Queen</font>
<font color="#00ffff">is not of sound mind, sir?</font>

01:52.760 --> 01:56.760
Let us say, Peel, that her wits are
fragile.

01:57.680 --> 02:01.720
I suspect that the cares of office
are proving too much for her.

02:02.680 --> 02:06.280
<font color="#ffff00">WELLINGTON: I'm sure the Duchess of</font>
<font color="#ffff00">Kent would be delighted to step in,</font>

02:06.320 --> 02:09.320
<font color="#ffff00">and, of course, Sir John Conroy</font>
<font color="#ffff00">would be at her side.</font>

02:09.360 --> 02:13.680
Conroy? The Duchess would need
the appointment of a co-regent.

02:14.440 --> 02:16.400
<font color="#ffff00">Of royal blood?</font>

02:16.440 --> 02:17.960
Precisely.

02:18.280 --> 02:23.240
They're all waiting for me to speak.
I can never think of anything
interesting to say.

02:23.280 --> 02:26.200
<font color="#ffff00">Everything the Queen says is</font>
<font color="#ffff00">interesting.</font>

02:26.240 --> 02:29.800
That is the third time you've looked
at your pocket watch since we
arrived.

02:29.840 --> 02:31.880
Do you have a more pressing
appointment?

02:31.920 --> 02:34.560
<font color="#ffff00">There's an anti-slavery bill</font>
<font color="#ffff00">going through Parliament.</font>

02:34.600 --> 02:36.120
<font color="#ffff00">I'm worried about its outcome.</font>

02:36.160 --> 02:38.200
Surely slavery was abolished a long
time ago?

02:38.240 --> 02:40.440
<font color="#ffff00">It's still legal</font>
<font color="#ffff00">in some Caribbean islands.</font>

02:40.480 --> 02:44.240
<font color="#ffff00">The Tories have taken up the cause</font>
<font color="#ffff00">because they think it can bring down</font>
<font color="#ffff00">my government.</font>

02:44.280 --> 02:46.920
Can't I do something about it? As
Queen?

02:46.960 --> 02:49.080
If it's known that I support
abolition...

02:49.120 --> 02:50.960
<font color="#ffff00">Liberals would applaud your good</font>
<font color="#ffff00">sense,</font>

02:51.000 --> 02:53.440
<font color="#ffff00">Tories would think</font>
<font color="#ffff00">I'd filled your head with bunkum.</font>

02:53.480 --> 02:56.160
And if I insist?
<font color="#ffff00">You cannot, Ma'am.</font>

02:56.200 --> 03:00.200
<font color="#ffff00">Advise, yes, encourage certainly,</font>
<font color="#ffff00">even warn,</font>

03:00.240 --> 03:02.440
<font color="#ffff00">but you cannot insist.</font>

03:04.520 --> 03:06.240
<font color="#00ffff">Such a splendid day.</font>

03:06.720 --> 03:10.600
<font color="#00ffff">Did you hear the crowds cheering me,</font>
<font color="#00ffff">Drina? It was most flattering.</font>

03:10.640 --> 03:14.960
<font color="#00ff00">I think the people would appreciate</font>
<font color="#00ff00">it if the Duchess were given a title</font>

03:15.000 --> 03:17.240
<font color="#00ff00">that reflects her position.</font>

03:18.720 --> 03:20.880
<font color="#00ff00">The Queen Mother.</font>

03:20.920 --> 03:22.280
<font color="#00ff00">That seems fitting to me.</font>

03:22.320 --> 03:24.840
But your current title
belonged to poor dear Papa.

03:24.880 --> 03:27.040
I see no reason to change it.

03:28.280 --> 03:29.880
<font color="#00ffff">Your Majesty.</font>

03:34.440 --> 03:37.120
<font color="#00ff00">Surprised you're not at the House,</font>
<font color="#00ff00">my lord.</font>

03:37.160 --> 03:41.160
<font color="#00ff00">I hear the vote is very close.</font>

03:42.800 --> 03:47.920
<font color="#ffff00">Ma'am, sorry to desert you but I'm</font>
<font color="#ffff00">afraid I've been called back to the</font>
<font color="#ffff00">House.</font>

03:47.960 --> 03:50.520
Now?
<font color="#ffff00">Please forgive me.</font>

03:53.880 --> 03:58.000
LORD CHAMBERLAIN:
The Honourable Lord Hastings.

03:58.040 --> 04:01.320
I say to the House that if slavery
is abolished in Jamaica,

04:01.360 --> 04:04.600
then the economy of the island
will be imperilled.

04:04.640 --> 04:06.400
(Crowd murmurs)

04:10.120 --> 04:14.400
<font color="#ffff00">And I say to the noble lord that a</font>
<font color="#ffff00">moral principle cannot be ignored</font>

04:14.440 --> 04:16.160
<font color="#ffff00">simply because it is inconvenient.</font>

04:16.200 --> 04:17.720
(Murmuring)

04:17.760 --> 04:22.440
<font color="#ffff00">This barbaric practice must be</font>
<font color="#ffff00">abhorrent to all civilised people.</font>

04:22.480 --> 04:23.840
(Murmuring)

04:26.040 --> 04:30.520
<font color="#00ff00">My lords, some decorum if you</font>
<font color="#00ff00">please!</font>

